    <note>Li(2) Bing [8082] His ancestors were Longxi jun Li(2), members of the Tang imperial clan. He was originally a Jizhou, Juye xian person, who moved to Quanzhou, Nanan xian with the flight south at the beginning of the Southern Song. His father-in-law, Ren(1) Li [3429] was probably was related to the Caozhou, Jiyin Ren (e.g., [875], [876], [877]) where one lineage branch of Bing's clan settled. Bing was the father-in-law of Fu(5) Zixiu's [625] brother, Zide [3309]. This lineage branch of the Fu(5) clan had moved from Mengzhou, Jiyuan to Quanzhou, Jinjiang at the beginning of the Southern Song (However, Bing is listed as a Quanzhou resident in the Fujian TZ jinshi list [148.5b]). The address of Fu(5) Yaoyu [627], the granduncle of Zixiu, was Mengzhou, Jiyuan xian. Another of Bing's sons-in-law was Chao(2) Zihe [3026], who had the same generational name as Chao(2) Gongwu's [11] and Chao(2) Gongmai's [12] sons and nephews. Zhou Bida, WJ, 69.12b-18b. CBD, 2, 838-9.</note>
